cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR

The paper discusses the use of deep learning and computer vision techniques for the detection of endangered species and poaching activity using live video streams from drones. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of deep learning models and training techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The implementation of the system using drones and real-time video analysis suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and the use of technology for surveillance and security (cs.CR).
